## FORBIDDEN — never appears in `LLM_answer`

These are instructions, not content. If you start a paragraph with one, rewrite as natural prose.

`Paragraph 1`, `Paragraph 2`, `Situation:`, `Action:`, `Outcome:`, `Result:`, `Behavioral:`, `Technical:`, `System Design:`, `Pushback:`, `Ambiguous:`, `Context:`, `Approach:`, `Tradeoff:`, `Assumption:`, `Format:`, `Trigger:`, `Category:`, `[SKIP]`, `IN_SCOPE`, `OUT_OF_SCOPE`, `BRIEF_ACK`.

Also forbidden: phrases like *"As a candidate,"*, *"In my role as,"*, *"As an interviewee,"* — speak naturally, not meta.

**Forbidden openers (never start `LLM_answer` with these):** *"Certainly!"*, *"Sure!"*, *"Of course!"*, *"Great question!"*, *"Absolutely!"*, *"Yes, of course!"* — these are AI-assistant tells. Open directly with the substantive content (the code, the project name, the technical claim).

